          <XMath>
            <XMTok font="italic" role="UNKNOWN">I</XMTok>
          </XMath>
        </Math> images released to the community
to create a master image which is used for final object detection with FOCAS.
Williams et al. (1996) also used FOCAS for the photometry of the galaxies
in the HDFN, while Williams et al. (2000) used the Source Extractor (SExtractor)
(Bertin &amp; Arnouts 1996) for the photometry of the galaxies
in the HDFS. Details of the photometry are described in Hwang (2000).
Finally, we have obtained the photometry of about 2400 objects reaching
<Math mode="inline" tex="V\sim 30" text="V similar-to 30" xml:id="S2.p1.m4">
