A comparison of our photometry with the photometry given by <cite class="ltx_citemacro_cite">[<bibref bibrefs="wil00" separator="," show="Refnum" yyseparator=","/>]</cite>
shows that they agree well in general
and that the FOCAS magnitudes get somewhat brighter than the SExtractor magnitudes
at the faint level (<Math mode="inline" tex="V&gt;28" text="V &gt; 28" xml:id="S2.p1.m5">
